Template\\n\\nThis notebook is a reusable template for symbolic tensor \
computations with a generic metric. It uses indexed coordinates rather than \
named ones, and leaves space for extra parameters such as a Carter constant, \
mass, spin, or cosmological constant.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. \
Setup\\n\\n```wl\\nClearAll[\\n  coordinateCount, coordinateNames, \
parameterNames, parameters, metricMatrix,\\n  inverseMetricMatrix, \
christoffel, riemann, ricciMatrix, ricciScalar,\\n  einsteinMatrix, \
printMatrix\\n];\\n\\n(* ==== CONFIGURATION SECTION ==== *)\\ncoordinateCount \
= 4;\\ncoordinateNames = Array[Subscript[x, #] &, coordinateCount];\\n\\n(* \
Add as many parameters as needed here *)\\nparameterNames = {Subscript[m, 1], \
Subscript[m, 2], Subscript[a], Subscript[q], Subscript[\[CapitalLambda]], \
Subscript[Q], Subscript[C, 1]};\\nparameters = \
AssociationThread[parameterNames, parameterNames];\\n\\n(* Generic symmetric \
metric matrix:\\n   Replace these entries with your desired metric \
components.\\n   You can include any of the parameters above, or add more. *)\
\\nmetricMatrix = {\\n  {g11[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g12[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g13[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g14[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]]},\\n  {g12[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g22[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g23[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g24[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]]},\\n  {g13[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g23[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g33[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g34[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]]},\\n  {g14[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g24[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g34[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]], g44[Sequence @@ coordinateNames, Sequence @@ \
Values[parameters]]}\\n};\\n\\nprintMatrix[label_, mat_] := (Print[label]; \
Print[MatrixForm[mat]]);\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Metric and inverse \
metric\\n\\n```wl\\nPrint[\\\"===== Generic Metric Workflow \
